<p>Here are three key features to consider:</p>



<ul>
<li><strong>Stop-limit orders:</strong> Set a stop price and a limit price to automatically trigger a buy or sell order when the market reaches a certain price point. This can help protect your profits or limit your losses in a volatile market.</li>



<li><strong>Trailing stop orders: </strong>Set a dynamic stop price that adjusts as the market price fluctuates. This allows you to lock in profits as the market rises, while protecting against potential losses if the market reverses.</li>



<li><strong>OCO (One Cancels the Other) orders: </strong>Place two orders simultaneously, with one being cancelled if the other is executed. This strategy can be useful when you&#8217;re unsure about the market direction and want to hedge your bets.</li>
</ul>



